Refactor macOS setup scripts for improved package management and documentation
- Updated README.md to clarify the transition from environment-based setup to package groups, enhancing user understanding of the setup process. - Refactored setup scripts to utilize a more modular YAML configuration, allowing for dynamic management of package groups instead of environments. - Improved the setup.zsh script to streamline package installation processes and enhance error handling. - Removed deprecated environment management functions from config.zsh, focusing on package group management for better clarity and maintainability. - Enhanced user guidance in setup.zsh with clearer instructions for configuring package groups. - Overall improvements to the structure and usability of the macOS setup process, aligning with previous enhancements for configurability and user experience.

Enhance setup.zsh and config.zsh with help message and refactor environment management
- Added a help message to setup.zsh for improved user guidance on script usage and options. - Removed functions for enabling, disabling, and listing environments from config.zsh to streamline the codebase. - Refactored get_enabled_environments and get_environment_packages functions for better clarity and efficiency. - Improved error messages in validate_config for clearer feedback on missing fields in environment configurations.
These changes enhance the usability and maintainability of the macOS setup scripts, aligning with previous enhancements for configurability and user experience.

Enhance macOS setup scripts with modular YAML configuration and improved error handling
- Updated README.md to introduce new features and enhance clarity on environment-based setup. - Refactored setup scripts to utilize a YAML configuration file for dynamic management of environments and packages. - Improved error handling and logging mechanisms across setup functions for better user feedback. - Introduced new modules for system checks and package installation, enhancing the robustness of the setup process. - Removed outdated GitHub Actions workflow for testing, streamlining the CI/CD process. - Enhanced test suite with comprehensive tests for environment setup, package installation, and error recovery.
These changes significantly improve the configurability, reliability, and user experience of the macOS setup process.
